  "cause_of_loss": "Aircraft flew into high-tension power cables",
  "narrative": "A training tragedy. The Lancaster was brand new — only 12 hours on the airframe. The crew were partway through their Heavy Conversion Unit course. Taking off from Winthorpe for a night navigation exercise, the aircraft barely made it 8 miles before crashing. Investigation found the aircraft struck the ground flat and on an even keel with all engines under power — the most likely cause was contact with high-tension cables. The crew was multinational: two Australians, one Canadian, and four British, aged 20 to 34.",
